				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">FINALLY, some answers.
<br />

<br />
First, I'd like to thank Danille for somewhat rewording the letter i originally sent. Here's the revision:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Hi Brelno/Alan, 
<br />

<br />
I worked on the Magician Q & A letter with Xalmat and edited the somewhat hostile tone of the first draft. Hopefully it now properly addresses the concerns of the mage class and nto come across as an attack against you or SoE. 
<br />

<br />
It has been reformated into easy to answer questions and in some cases I have provided examples of the detail that the magicians would like to see in some of the answers.
<br />

<br />
Hopefully you can respond to these questions now.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for your consideration and if you have any questions please let me know.
<br />

<br />
Danille Impholder
<br />

<br />
E-mail follows:
<br />

<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
<br />

<br />
John Smedley, Alan Crosby, and the entire EverQuest development team, 
<br />

<br />
On behalf of the Magician community, I thank you for this opportunity for 
<br />
reading this feedback and for answering our questions. Some of the common feelings that the mage community has right now are the following:
<br />

<br />
1)-Class imbalance due to level increases, mob difficulty increases, 
<br />
and limitations in mage class abilities and spells. 
<br />

<br />
2)-The low/mid level common player feels some alienation, and focusing on the high-end player base. (aka uber-guilds, providing little or no benefit to low and mid level players, and providing heavy emphasis on the high level player base).
<br />

<br />
3)-Most players yearn for the fantasy role-play aspects of the game, (dragons etc., instead of the "alien" themes that seem out of context with traditional lore. (Wayfarers type stuff)
<br />

<br />
4)-Looking to add more "fun" by adding back in, among other things, the "Quest" in "EverQuest." 
<br />

<br />
The Magician community addresses the representatives of the EverQuest 
<br />
development team and seeks to find out more about the new expansion. 
<br />

<br />
However, before we can understand Omens of War, we must understand the 
<br />
Magician class further. We yearn to know the current state of the Magician 
<br />
class. Therefore, I present these specific questions. 
<br />

<br />
1)-What is Sony Online Entertainment's definition of the Magician class and what is our role in solo, group and raid situations? (Example: Mages strength is thru their pet and their pet is second to none… their nukes are…. their summoning ability is…) 
<br />

<br />
2)-What is our relative damage rank among all of the "DPS" classes? (Melee/caster: example 
<br />

<br />
short term: wizard > magician + pet > rogue > monk ~ ranger ~ berserker? ~ necro? > beastlord? > mage w/o pet ~ druid > warrior ~ shadowknight > paladins (minus Slay Undead) > bard  > rest…
<br />

<br />
long term (10 minutes +): rogue > necro? > monk ~ ranger~ berserker? ~ mage + pet > beastlord? > the rest)
<br />

<br />
3)-What is our relative damage rank among just the spell caster classes?
<br />

<br />
(Short term, burst fights, wizards > mages > necro….mid term, mages > wizard ~ necro...long term, necro > mages ~ wizard)
<br />

<br />
4)-Are we, the premier pet class? (If so, why are we less capable of supporting our pets as other classes? Example: Why are Magician pet heals so lacking?  Why are Dire Charm pets perceived as out-damaging our pets? 
<br />

<br />
5)-Are we, or are we not, a soloing class? If we are, why is soloing from level 61 beyond far less viable than it was from levels 1 to 60? Why do many classes (especially classes able to Kite and Quad-Kite) have a superior solo advantage? 
<br />

<br />
6)-At this point in the game, (GoD) why is the Magician the only caster that has no way to survive a hostile environment except Gate? In GoD, our pets routinely get one rounded.
<br />

<br />
The members of the Magician community also want to know answers to the 
<br />
following class balance issues: 
<br />

<br />
1)-Why are druids overall a better nuke class (not even looking at their DoT damage) than Magicians? [Note: As of June 9th, Test server was patched to bridge the gaps between Magician and Druid post-level-63 nukes. However, Druids still retain their nuking advantage from levels 1 to 62, and 63+ with Quick Damage] 
<br />

<br />
2)-Is our pet expected to cover the full range of abilities (Root, Snare, etc) 
<br />
that other classes have? 
<br />

<br />
3)-Where are the pet-specific focus items? (Aeromancy, Aquamancy, Geomancy, 
<br />
Pyromancy)
<br />

<br />
4)-When will the issues with the 51+ fire pets be resolved? This pet has been 99% ineffective for over a 4 years now. It is never used.
<br />

<br />
5)-Will Magicians receive a form of defense other than their pet, that is usable by a 
<br />
level 50 mage with zero AA? 
<br />

<br />
6)-Why was the summoned population of Plane of Fire changed to monster classification, while summoned beings in Planes of Earth and Air were left untouched? 
<br />

<br />
7)-Will pets ever return to high (invulnerable or near) resists to specific element AoEs? 
<br />

<br />
There are several things known about the new expansion. However, the 
<br />
Magician community seeks more specific answers to the following questions. 
<br />

<br />
1)-What is the expected level range for Omens of War zones? 
<br />

<br />
2)-Related to the above question, will the Gates expansion be required to gain access to Omens zones? 
<br />

<br />
3)-Will the Epic 2.0 be accessible to Non-Time-equipped players? 
<br />

<br />
4)-Will the Epic 2.0 quests be mostly 1 group able, or will raids be required for most parts of the epic? 
<br />

<br />
5)-Will summoned creatures be put into the new (and re-introduced into existing) zones so we can use our line of “anti-summoned” spells? 
<br />

<br />
6)-Related to the question above, will there be a continuation of the summoned-charm and summoned-mesmerization spell lines? (Will the lvl restrictions (lvl 60) be removed to eliminate the current situation of only have one zone that a lvl 65 player can use them in? 
<br />

<br />
7)-Will a large number of Omens zones be seeded as usually with dire charm-able (normal, animal, and undead) creatures? If so, how many will also be seeded with 
<br />
level 60 summoned and charm able creatures? (This is a sore point for mages)
<br />

<br />
8)-Will there be any new spell lines for Magicians? In general? 
<br />

<br />
9)-Will existing IV focus items and focus items from the Elemental Planes and 
<br />
beyond be usable from level 66 and up? 
<br />

<br />
10)-Will Magicians be receiving any kind of aggro reducing abilities or spells? 
<br />

<br />
11)-Will spells in Omens be common, similar to Kunark, Luclin, and Planes of 
<br />
Power, or will they be rare and hard to obtain, leaving only the elite few 
<br />
to collect them? (Many players want spells to be handled as they were in Kunark, Luclin [tradable] or like PoP (spells be tradable thru no drop parchments) rather than in Gates NO DROP period end of story? 
<br />

<br />
12)-Will there be new content for low to mid level players?
<br />

<br />
13)-Will the new Task System be implemented for ALL levels of characters? 
<br />

<br />
14)-Will magicians get the needed resist modifiers to our damage spells that 
<br />
all other dps casters (dru/wiz/nec) get? (Even bards were given a -50 resist 
<br />
modifier in their attack spells recently) 
<br />

<br />
15)-Are there plans for an upgraded Mod Rod in Omens? 
<br />

<br />
Finally, the community wants to know about the state of Everquest's future. 
<br />

<br />
1)-Will Everquest evolve to being a more traditional fantasy role-playing game (dragons, etc., instead of the alien/wayfarers themes of Shadows of Luclin, Gates of Discord, and apparently Omens of War? 
<br />

<br />
2)-Will Role-playing become a significant part of game play again? 
<br />

<br />
3)-Will there be new models for pets and elemental form AA’s in Omens of War and the new graphics engine? Will they be humanoid to allow riding on mounts while under an elemental illusion? 
<br />

<br />
4)-Will there be a second class summit at SoE? May the mage community select a representative to go?
<br />

<br />
5)-What is being done to ensure the longevity and survivability of EverQuest 
<br />
in the current MMORPG market? 
<br />

<br />
Thanks for your review of these concerns and questions. The edit was done in a good faith effort to resume the dialogue necessary for addressing the mage community's concerns.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely,
<br />

<br />
Complied by -Sage Xalmat Lunaire 
<br />
Arch Convoker of Brell Serilis 
<br />
Lead Librarian/Forum Moderator 
<br />
The Mage Compendium 
