			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here's Brenlo's response. The questions posed will be bolded, with his response below.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I will answer the few that I can, however anything relating to class definition or DPS will not be answered at this time and most likely not for a few months.
<br />
 
<br />
Most of this stuff is best addressed by Rytan.  I will see if I can get answers from him.
<br />
 
<br />
Here is what I have for you now.  I will send along any other answers as I get them.
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">1)-What is the expected level range for Omens of War zones?</span>   OoW is expected to be for level 45 and above.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">2)-Related to the above question, will the Gates expansion be required to gain access to Omens zones?</span>
<br />
Nope it will not.  You will be able to access the Omens expansion without the requirement of previous expansions.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">3)-Will the Epic 2.0 be accessible to Non-Time-equipped players?</span>
<br />
Epic 1.5 will definitely be available to those who have not conquered Time.  However epic 2.0 will require a more hardy adventurer.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">4)-Will the Epic 2.0 quests be mostly 1 group able, or will raids be required for most parts of the epic?</span>
<br />
There will be a good mix which will require some raid time and some group time.  However the raids will have other rewards that will provide incentive other than just getting epic pieces.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">5)-Will summoned creatures be put into the new (and re-introduced into existing) zones so we can use our line of “anti-summoned” spells?</span>
<br />
I am sure that there will be some creatures flagged as summoned, however I would expect that the number will not increase from what we have added in other expansions.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">6)-Related to the question above, will there be a continuation of the summoned-charm and summoned-mesmerization spell lines? (Will the lvl restrictions (lvl 60) be removed to eliminate the current situation of only have one zone that a lvl 65 player can use them in?</span>
<br />
Spells are still being worked on so I do not know.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">7)-Will a large number of Omens zones be seeded as usually with dire charm-able (normal, animal, and undead) creatures? If so, how many will also be seeded with 
<br />
level 60 summoned and charm able creatures? (This is a sore point for mages)</span>
<br />
I sure hope so. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">8)-Will there be any new spell lines for Magicians? In general?</span>
<br />
Rytan is still putting spells together, so we do not know what the final spell list will look like yet.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">9)-Will existing IV focus items and focus items from the Elemental Planes and 
<br />
beyond be usable from level 66 and up?</span>
<br />
Yes, we are trying to figure out how useful though.
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">12)-Will there be new content for low to mid level players?</span>
<br />
The task system will have lots for low and mid level players to do.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">13)-Will the new Task System be implemented for ALL levels of characters?</span>
<br />
Yes. Initially it will be for levels 1 to 50, however we plan to extend it to all levels.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">1)-Will Everquest evolve to being a more traditional fantasy role-playing game (dragons, etc., instead of the alien/wayfarers themes of Shadows of Luclin, Gates of Discord, and apparently Omens of War?</span>
<br />
EverQuest is still mostly a traditional fantasy setting.  Some zones have expanded to include other content, however most content is of the traditional sort and yes we do plan to continue with the traditional fantasy genre.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">2)-Will Role-playing become a significant part of game play again?</span>
<br />
Role playing is up to you folks.  We cannot force you to roleplay.  It has to be something that you choose to do.  
<br />
 
<br />
If you are refering to factions having an increased role, then yes the team would like to do more with factions.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">3)-Will there be new models for pets and elemental form AA’s in Omens of War and the new graphics engine? Will they be humanoid to allow riding on mounts while under an elemental illusion?</span>
<br />
At some point we will add new models for pets and elemental forms, although I doubt they will be allowed to ride mounts.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">4)-Will there be a second class summit at SoE? May the mage community select a representative to go?</span>
<br />
We do plan to have Guild Summits on a regular basis and yes I plan to invite someone from the Magicians Tower, space permitting.
<br />

<br />
As to EQ's future.  We have the next 18 months planned out and do not plan to go away anytime soon.
<br />

<br />
Alan Crosby
<br />
Community Relations Manager</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
