<br />

<br />
1- I garantee that many of us could each list a broken or completely obsolete quest and never overlap each other.
<br />

<br />
2- Let me put forth my own concern.  I have now officially reached the 115 hour mark, which gives me a total count of 5 feathered leggings from Quillmane.  While this isnt necessarily <span style="font-weight: bold">broken</span>, this particular  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_wall.gif" alt="Brick wall" border="0" /> 
<br />
part of our epic is just plain sickening.  At one point any Mage who has worked on their epic has read posts in this forum, et al, of Mages with horror stories ranging in the 200+ hours without getting a cloak.  Furthermore, this part of the epic itself is clearly out of whack.  At no point pre level 50 did I want to come to this zone to hunt as a mage, even if I had, finding Quillmane without a tracker would have been like winning the lottery.  Group... good luck dragging people of any level out to this zone.  
<br />

<br />
With those 2 points as a very small basis, I would suggest that soe will likely never fix, or alter any quests that are pre-PoP.  Mage epic (only) included in that.  If some of you dont know, they have facilitated obtaining certain things for other class' epics.  
<br />

<br />
Bah I better stop before this becomes a rant.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_silenced.gif" alt="Silenced" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
